24.38	Kamui_Kobayashi	Kamui Kobayashi	Kamui Kobayashi Kobayashi Kamui, born September 13, 1986 in Amagasaki, Hyogo, Japan) is a Japanese racing driver. He has competed in the GP2 Series, won the GP2 Asia Series, and made his Formula One debut with Toyota in the final two races of 2009 when he replaced Timo Glock after the German was injured in a crash during qualifying for the Japanese Grand Prix. He has driven for Sauber since the 2010 season. He was named after Kamuy, divine being in Ainu mythology, and the letter of the name imitated the sound citing three Kanjis from the sentence "Enabling great dream(s)".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/17/Kamui_Kobayashi_2010_Malaysia.jpg/220px-Kamui_Kobayashi_2010_Malaysia.jpg
